<h5>
What is E-Service?</h5>
<p>E-Service is an online ordering tool for Australian customers who wish to order Cengage Learning Australia products online.<br />
<br />
</p>
<h5>
How do I place an order online?</h5>
<strong>
<h6>Search&nbsp;</h6>
</strong>Search tools are helpful when using any website. Within our Cengage Learning Australia website we have numerous ways to search for our products such as:<br />
<strong>
Normal Browse</strong> Click onto any aspect of our website, such as department, browse bar or top navigation bar.<br />
<strong>
Simple Search</strong> Where you can enter your search word(s) or phrases in the box provided. <a>Click here</a> to go to this section.<br />
<strong>
Advanced Search</strong> Where you can search by Book Title, Author, ISBN, State/Territory listing, or by Category or Year Level. <a href="/contact-us">Click here</a> to go to this section.<br />
<br />
<h6>
Substitute items or Particular Editions</h6>
Presently, we do not have the facility to order particular editions other than the latest edition or a &ldquo;Do Not Substitute&rdquo; facility on our website. If you need either of these facilities, please contact <a href="/contact-us">Customer Service</a><br />
<br />
<h6>
Add to Basket</h6>
After you have entered the &ldquo;Consumers&rdquo; section within the E-Service Centre you are now ready to make purchases.<br />
To add to your basket, you can either click &ldquo;Add to basket&rdquo; next to the title you wish to purchase in the subject section within that department.<br />
Or alternatively click onto the title of the book and then click &ldquo;Add to basket&rdquo; located in the right hand side navigational bar highlighted in orange.&nbsp;<br />
After you have done so you will notice that &ldquo;<em>This item has been added to your basket</em>&rdquo; appears above the title of the book you have selected.<br />
<br />
<h6>
View Basket&nbsp;</h6>
After you have selected your purchases or you wish to view your purchases at any time press the &ldquo;View Basket&rdquo; icon located either on the left hand-side navigational pane or the right-handside navigational pane if you are in the book details section.&nbsp;<br />
This will open up &ldquo;Your Order&rdquo;, which can be modified at any time within your visit.<br />
<br />
<h6>
Deleting Items&nbsp;</h6>
If you would like to delete any of the items off your order, change the quantity to &ldquo;0&rdquo; against the title and press the &ldquo;Update Cart&rdquo; button.<br />
<br />
<h6>
Changing Quantities&nbsp;</h6>
This is very similar to deleting items except rather than reducing the quantity to 0, you can change the quantity to whatever number you desire. Make sure to press the &ldquo;Update Cart&rdquo; button after you do this.<br />
<br />
<h6>
Checkout&nbsp;</h6>
Now you are ready to &ldquo;Checkout&rdquo; your books. Press the &ldquo;Proceed to Checkout&rdquo; button. Fill in your contact details, address details and credit card details. Once you have finished in the checkout section your order has been processed and you will receive a reference number. Please keep this number for your personal records.<br />
<br />
<h5>
Can I return my book?&nbsp;</h5>
All online credit card orders are firm sale which means that titles can not be returned.&nbsp;<br />
If there is a problem with your order, a title is received misbound or damaged contact Customer Service<br />
<br />
